result.execSummary:
The defendant Shawn R. Dailey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Shawn R. Dailey in court with attorney Timothy Luke Angel.  Larry Eugene Nelson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court hears DA Nelson. Defendant Shawn R. Dailey in court with attorney Timothy Luke Angel.  Larry Eugene Nelson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
State heard on Prior Conviction Motion.  Original motion encompassed two priors, discussion of third prior.  State argues in favor of motion, citing State v. Smith.  Defense opposes motion and gives argument on age of convictions.  Priors discussed, determined once the defendant decides whether or not to testify then the Court can sidebar this issue further.
Instruction on self defense discussed.  State argues against any instruction inferring to self defense, gives reasons.  Defense responds - doesn't plan to introduce a self defense argument.  Parties concur.
State advises amended complaint was filed.  Request for NG plea on the counts.  Defense objects to timeliness of filing the amended complaint but would agree to the NG plea.  Court will allow amended charge(s).  NG plea entered.
Discussion on witnesses.
Trial to commence on time, at 9:00 am.
